summary: This module provides the functionality required to access and manipulate data stored in a MySQL database.
description:
Module overview

This module provides the functionality required to access and manipulate data stored in a MySQL database.

Prerequisite: Add the MySQL driver JAR as a native library dependency in your Ballerina project. This module uses database properties from the MySQL version 8.0.x onwards. Therefore, it is recommended to use a MySQL driver version greater than 8.0.x. Then, once you build the project by executing the ballerina build command, you should be able to run the resultant JAR by executing the java -jar command.

E.g., The Ballerina.toml content. Change the path to the JDBC driver appropriately.

[project]
org-name= "sample"
version= "0.1.0"

[platform]
target = "java8"

    [[platform.libraries]]
    artafactId = "mysql-connector-java"
    version = "8.0.17"
    path = "/path/to/mysql-connector-java-8.0.17.jar"
    groupId = "mysql"
    modules = ["samplemodule"]

Else, if you're trying to run a single BAL file, you can copy the JDBC driver into the ${BALLERINA_HOME}/bre/lib directory and run the BAL file by executing the ballerina run command.

Client

To access a database, you must first create a mysql:Client object. The examples for creating a MySQL client can be found below.

Creating a client

This example shows different ways of creating the mysql:Client.

The client can be created with an empty constructor and hence, the client will be initialized with the default properties. The first example with the dbClient1 demonstrates this.

The dbClient2 receives the host, username, and password. Since the properties are passed in the same order as it is defined in the jdbc:Client, you can pass it without named params.

The dbClient3 uses the named params to pass the attributes since it is skipping some params in the constructor. Further mysql:Options is passed to configure the SSL and connection timeout in the MySQL client.

Similarly, the dbClient4 uses the named params and it provides an unshared connection pool in the type of sql:ConnectionPool to be used within the client. For more details about connection pooling, see the SQL Module.

mysql:Client|sql:Error dbClient1 = new ();
mysql:Client|sql:Error dbClient2 = new ("localhost", "rootUser", "rooPass", 
                              "information_schema", 3306);
                              
mysql:Options mysqlOptions = {
  ssl: {
    mode: mysql:SSL_PREFERRED
  },
  connectTimeoutInSeconds: 10
};
mysql:Client|sql:Error dbClient3 = new (user = "rootUser", password = "rootPass",
                              options = mysqlOptions);
mysql:Client|sql:Error dbClient4 = new (user = "rootUser", password = "rootPass",
                              connectionPool = {maxOpenConnections: 5});

You can find more details about each property in the mysql:Client constructor.

The mysql:Client references sql:Client and all the operations defined by the sql:Client will be supported by the mysql:Client as well.

For more information on all the operations supported by the mysql:Client, which include the below, see the SQL Module.

  1. Connection Pooling
  2. Querying data
  3. Inserting data
  4. Updating data
  5. Deleting data
  6. Batch insert and update data
  7. Closing client

fields.name: connectTimeoutInSeconds
fields.description: Timeout to be used when connecting to the mysql server

fields.name: socketTimeoutInSeconds
fields.description: Socket timeout during the read/write operations with mysql server, 0 means no socket timeout

fields.name: mode
fields.description: SSLMode to be used during the connection

records.name: SSLConfig
records.description: SSL Configuration to be used when connecting to mysql server.

parameters.name: sqlQuery
parameters.description: The query which needs to be executed as string or ParameterizedQuery when the SQL query has params to be passed in

parameters.name: rowType
parameters.description: The typedesc of the record that should be returned as a result. If this is not provided the default column names of the query result set be used for the record attributes

returnParameters.description: Stream of records in the type of rowType

remoteMethods.name: query
remoteMethods.description: Queries the database with the query provided by the user, and returns the result as stream.

parameters.name: sqlQuery
parameters.description: The DDL or DML query such as INSERT, DELETE, UPDATE, etc as string or ParameterizedQuery when the query has params to be passed in

returnParameters.description: Summary of the sql update query as ExecutionResult or returns Error if any error occurred when executing the query

remoteMethods.name: execute
remoteMethods.description: Executes the DDL or DML sql queries provided by the user, and returns summary of the execution.

parameters.name: sqlQueries
parameters.description: The DDL or DML query such as INSERT, DELETE, UPDATE, etc as ParameterizedQuery with an array of values passed in.

returnParameters.description: Summary of the executed SQL queries as ExecutionResult[] which includes details such as affectedRowCount and lastInsertId. If one of the commands in the batch fails, this function will return BatchExecuteError, however the JDBC driver may or may not continue to process the remaining commands in the batch after a failure. The summary of the executed queries in case of error can be accessed as (<sql:BatchExecuteError> result).detail()?.executionResults.

remoteMethods.name: batchExecute
remoteMethods.description: Executes a batch of parameterised DDL or DML sql query provided by the user, and returns the summary of the execution.

parameters.name: user
parameters.description: If the mysql server is secured, the username to be used to connect to the mysql server

parameters.name: password
parameters.description: The password of provided username of the database

parameters.name: database
parameters.description: The name fo the database to be connected

parameters.name: port
parameters.description: Port number of the mysql server to be connected

parameters.name: options
parameters.description: The Database specific JDBC client properties

parameters.name: connectionPool
parameters.description: The sql:ConnectionPool object to be used within the jdbc client. If there is no connectionPool is provided, the global connection pool will be used and it will be shared by other clients which has same properties
